Ibi Giga Ambassadors, a political group in Ondo State, has appointed 203 Ward Coordinators to campaign for the re-election of Gov. Oluwarotimi Akeredolu in the 2020 guber election in the state.  The Convener of the group, Chief Alex Ajipe, said in a statement in Akure on Thursday that the coordinators would engage in aggressive campaign in the 18 local government areas of the state. The convener urged the coordinators to dedicate their energy and expertise toward the success of the project. “All the coordinators and their secretaries need to publicise the achievements of government in the areas of industrialisation, infrastructure, health, education and agriculture,”Ajipe said. He also urged them to dedicate their energy and expertise toward the success of the project. Ajipe further said that all necessary arrangements had been made to provide palliatives to cushion the effects of the lockdown put in place in the state to check the spread of Covid-19.